tech.mcprison.prison.output

Class DisplayComponent

  • java.lang.Object
    • tech.mcprison.prison.output.DisplayComponent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BulletedListComponent, ButtonComponent, FancyMessageComponent, TextComponent

    public abstract class DisplayComponent
extends java.lang.Object
    A component that can be attached to a ChatDisplay. Display components add some text to the display in a certain way.

    API 1.0

      • text

        public abstract java.lang.String text()
        Returns the text that is being appended to the ChatDisplay. This should return the raw JSON if FancyMessage is involved. To retrieve a raw JSON string, call FancyMessage.toJSONString().
        Returns:
        The string of text to add.

      • send

        public abstract void send(CommandSender sender)
        Sends this DisplayComponent to the sender. This is called by the ChatDisplay, and is called in order of addition to it.
        Parameters:
        sender - The CommandSender to send this to.
